      "side": 1,
      "message": "This won\u0027t match on `definitely_not_atoi`. It\u0027s using AST identifiers rather than text matching. Here\u0027s an example to confirm:\n\n```\n  $ cat test.cpp  \n  int a \u003d atoi(\"42\");\n  int b \u003d std::atoi(\"42\");\n  int c \u003d definitely_not_atoi(\"42\");\n\n  $ ast-grep scan --rule common-errors.yml test.cpp\n  error[unsafe-int-parse]:\n    4 │     int a \u003d atoi(\"42\");\n      │             ^^^^^^^^^^\n  error[unsafe-int-parse]:\n    5 │     int b \u003d std::atoi(\"42\");\n      │             ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^\n```",
